Package io.smint.clapi.consumer.integration.core.jobs

Interface ISyncMetadataIdMapper

All Known Implementing Classes:
DefaultSyncMetadataIdMapperImpl
public interface ISyncMetadataIdMapper
Implementing classes manage a cache for mapping meta data's Smint.io API id to sync target ID - one-way, though.

All assets (BaseSyncAsset) have some structured meta data. Ideally the applied meta data are a bunch of references to the meta data definitions, stored elsewhere. Each storage uses IDs to enable references to it. Since we have two storage system to keep in sync, there are two regimes of IDs, the Smint.io API IDs and the sync target IDs. A mapping is required and this is what this cache is about. During synchronizing of all meta data, this cache is filled and then kept available until the next meta data synchronization, which rebuilds it anyway.

The mapping is one-way only, from Smint.io API to sync target ID - no reverse mapping.

    • addMappingOfContentProviders

      ISyncMetadataIdMapper addMappingOfContentProviders(ISmintIoMetadataElement[] metaDataElements)
      Adds mapping of Smint.io API IDs to sync target IDs for content providers.

      The Smint.io API ID is read from ISmintIoMetadataElement.getKey(), whereas the synchronization target ID is read from ISmintIoMetadataElement.getTargetMetadataUuid(). Both must not be null. An exception is thrown in case any meta data element lacks one of these values.

      In case one of the IDs already exist, it will override the previously existing mapping.

      Parameters:
      metaDataElements - the list of meta data elements to add to the mapping.
      Returns:
      this.
      Throws:
      NullPointerException - in case ISmintIoMetadataElement.getKey() or ISmintIoMetadataElement.getTargetMetadataUuid() is null for any item in the provided list.

    • getContentProviderId

      String getContentProviderId(String smintIoApiId)
      Maps the Smint.io ID of a Content Provider to a synchronization target ID/key.

      Each available content provider in the Smint.io platform needs a corresponding representation of the target side. This is necessary to track the origin of assets. Hence a one-to-one mapping is required. Therefore a direct translation of the IDs on both platforms (Smint.io + sync target) is necessary.

      Implementation of ISyncJob will make use of this target ID to provide prepared assets that can be easily compared to the data already available on the sync target.

      The Smint.io ID to map is similar to the value from ISmintIoAsset.getContentProvider().

      Parameters:
      smintIoApiId - the ID on the Smint.io platform.
      Returns:
      the key on the synchronization target, or null in case the item does not exist yet on the target or if parameter the is null.
      See Also:
      • ISmintIoAsset.getContentProvider()

    • getLicenseLanguageId

      String getLicenseLanguageId(String smintIoId)
      Maps the Smint.io ID of a License Language to a synchronization target ID/key.

      The Smint.io ID to map is similar to the value from ISmintIoLicenseTerm.getAllowedLanguages().

      Beware that the value "any" is used in addition to the ISO 639-3 codes, in order to denote any language. There is not ISO code for that case.

      Parameters:
      smintIoId - the ID on the Smint.io platform.
      Returns:
      the key on the synchronization target, or null in case the item does not exist yet on the target or if parameter the is null.
      See Also:
